ives and private family collections, this study reveals the depth of Ford's involvement in every aspect of this case and explains why Jewish civil rights lawyers and religious leaders were deeply divided over how to handle Ford.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aAnti-Jewish propagandazUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aAntisemitismzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aHate speechzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aTrials (Libel)zMichiganzDetroit. 7aHISTORY / United States / 20th Century.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804783736zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804783736423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804783736.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles